Dialogue: 0,0:00:-06.-60,0:00:-03.-02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world... Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:-03.00,0:00:00.-18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A world for you who seek freedom
Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.-16,0:00:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,stretches out right before your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.01,0:00:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If your endless dreams are your guide,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.01,0:00:15.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,surpass them, under the flag of your beliefs!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.19,0:00:21.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.69,0:00:26.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.20,0:00:31.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.37,0:00:39.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.71,0:00:47.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When the summer sun\Nsways the sails of my heart
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.82,0:00:57.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the cue to open the door to a new world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.33,0:01:04.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailing through the rocky waves of despair
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.34,0:01:11.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We head beyond the horizon
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.01,0:01:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Making a splash,\NI've just started on my search
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.68,0:01:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Heading towards a world without end
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.19,0:01:27.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My heart bursting with enthusiasm,\NI'll go to the ends of the earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.36,0:01:35.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In search of light yet unseen
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.07,0:01:46.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Steer for the Clouds! Capture the South Bird!"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.68,0:01:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you need to tell us, old guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.38,0:01:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here. I'll start by telling you\Neverything I know about the sky island.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.72,0:02:00.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of it's certain, but it's up to you\Nif you wanna believe it or not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.33,0:02:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah! We believe you!\N--Geez, you're fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.56,0:02:06.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a strange phenomenon\Nthat occurs in these waters--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.40,0:02:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,sometimes it'll turn to night,\Neven though it's the middle of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.90,0:02:13.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! We saw that! Right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.91,0:02:20.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Night came, and then\Nsome monsters appeared!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.41,0:02:21.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The giants?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.78,0:02:26.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a story about where they\Ncome from, but forget 'em for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.49,0:02:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This sudden nightfall...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's caused by the shadows\Nof extremely compact clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.36,0:02:39.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean cumulonimbus clouds?\NBut it was too dark to be clouds...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.87,0:02:42.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! You're so dumb, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.20,0:02:44.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It gets cloudy on days\Nwhen there's lots of clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.44,0:02:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Yeah! Cloudy!\N--Cloudy!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.67,0:02:48.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up and listen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.87,0:02:52.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are clouds known as\N"cumuloregalis clouds."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.34,0:02:57.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They pile high into the sky but\Nproduce no air currents or rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.75,0:03:03.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When they appear high in the sky,\Neven sunlight is blocked out,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.22,0:03:05.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bringing afternoon "nighttime" to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.92,0:03:09.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One theory has it that cumuloregalis\Nclouds are fossilized clouds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.46,0:03:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that have floated in the sky for\Nthousands and thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.73,0:03:18.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's ridiculous! Clouds with no\Nair currents even after building up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.87,0:03:21.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're free to believe they can't exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.54,0:03:24.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not asking you to believe me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.38,0:03:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're mystery clouds, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:29.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pretty much. There's still\Nno explanation for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.62,0:03:31.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're awesome, Luffy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.25,0:03:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. If a sky island really does exist...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.35,0:03:37.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that'd be the only possible place!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.29,0:03:40.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Gotcha! Let's go above those clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.03,0:03:42.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Get up, Zoro!\N--Huh? Is it morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.36,0:03:45.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get ready, everyone! Cloud rudder full!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.40,0:03:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for filling us in, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.53,0:03:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How many times do I gotta say\Nwe don't know how to get there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.87,0:03:54.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now comes the real problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.27,0:03:56.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me start by saying this...\NPut your lives on the line!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.24,0:03:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're already near death...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.24,0:04:01.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Knock-Up Stream is a\Ncurrent that shoots into the air...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.01,0:04:06.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can theoretically take it\Ninto the sky. Understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.32,0:04:10.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a current that can send ships flying, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.02,0:04:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Then it just needs to\Nsend us above the clouds!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.96,0:04:16.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.66,0:04:18.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On a current?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.30,0:04:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't we just end up\Nsmashing back into the ocean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.57,0:04:25.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Normally, yeah. The key is timing.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.00,0:04:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's easy to talk about\Nbeing sent up the current,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.28,0:04:37.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it's not gonna be as nice\Na trip as you guys think.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.82,0:04:41.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Knock-Up Stream is a natural disaster.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.09,0:04:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's something that should\Nnormally be avoided!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.86,0:04:49.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How exactly does a water\Ncurrent rise into the sky?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.26,0:04:53.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We've never heard of\Nanything like that before...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.70,0:04:56.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.74,0:05:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, we can only guess as to\Nhow that monstrous current works.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.84,0:05:05.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's dumb enough to\Njump in and find out, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.81,0:05:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The accepted theory goes like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.55,0:05:14.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Deep beneath the sea floor,\Nthere are large cavities,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.92,0:05:18.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and low-temperature\Nsea water seeps into them.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.32,0:05:21.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The heat from the earth below\Nturns that water into steam,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.93,0:05:25.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the resulting pressure causes\Nan explosion on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.33,0:05:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One big enough to send the sea flying\Nand create a current into the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.81,0:05:38.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For about one minute, the sea\Ncontinues to rise into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.71,0:05:43.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One minute?! What size of explosion\Nare we talking about here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.62,0:05:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The explosions change location each time,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.78,0:05:48.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and occur five times a month.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:51.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to be blown into smithereens...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.09,0:05:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, y'know,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.09,0:05:58.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,describing a grand natural phenomenon\Nwith words and logic is foolish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.10,0:06:04.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-So, basically, we gotta ride this current\Nthat only appears five times a month
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.37,0:06:06.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and hope the sky island shows up?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.51,0:06:14.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. And if you miss, you'll fall\Nback down, slam into the ocean...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.38,0:06:19.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and then you'll all end up\Nat the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.72,0:06:24.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Alright! Let's give up on the sky island!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.79,0:06:26.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.63,0:06:34.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You gotta have the luckiest luck\Nthat's ever lucked to make it there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.47,0:06:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be fine! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.44,0:06:37.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.70,0:06:41.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"We'll be fine"? How can you say\Nsuch groundless stuff so easily...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.64,0:06:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, just look at the Going Merry now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.74,0:06:47.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It looks so pitiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.08,0:06:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can't stand up to a\Ngigantic disaster like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.95,0:06:55.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's true. Even in mint condition,\Nthat ship wouldn't stand a chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.65,0:06:56.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.66,0:06:58.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Speed, weight, strength...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.96,0:07:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That boat'd be blasted apart in the explosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.06,0:07:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But... See! It really is impossible!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.53,0:07:09.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But don't you worry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.84,0:07:13.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have Masira and Shojo\Nhelp take you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.44,0:07:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only after we strengthen your ship, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Just leave it to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:20.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, guys!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.51,0:07:24.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't even ask us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.02,0:07:26.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Do you even understand?!\N--Understand what?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.52,0:07:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For starters... Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.59,0:07:33.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The most we can stay on\Nthis island is one more day!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.46,0:07:37.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the Log Pose will\Nstart pointing to the next island!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.80,0:07:40.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! Yeah! We won't make it in time!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.00,0:07:43.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, old man! You're not a psychic!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.60,0:07:45.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I doubt you know,\Nbut how many days will it be
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.87,0:07:50.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,until the Knock-Up Stream and\Nthe cumuloregalis clouds line up?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.84,0:07:55.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no! How many months?!\NNo, how many years?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.85,0:07:59.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow afternoon.\NIf you're going, you better get ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.15,0:08:01.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't make it in that time!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.12,0:08:06.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? If you don't like it, then just quit!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:08.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-You're lying!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.19,0:08:13.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This isn't right! We just met you today!\NAren't you being too nice?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.70,0:08:15.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.50,0:08:18.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hold on, Usopp!\N--Shut up, you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.20,0:08:20.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tomorrow just happens\Nto be the perfect chance
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.01,0:08:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to go to this legendary,\Nunknown "sky island"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.68,0:08:29.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you'll help strengthen\Nour ship and take us there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.85,0:08:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's way too convenient!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.52,0:08:33.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What exactly are you scheming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.92,0:08:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus you're Noland the Liar's\Ndescendant! We can't trust you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.29,0:08:45.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old-timer! Dinner's ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.53,0:08:46.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.67,0:08:51.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami-san! Dinner's--
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.70,0:08:54.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What?! Are you gonna fight?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.91,0:08:58.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever "midday night"\Nis confirmed in Masira's turf,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.08,0:09:03.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,cumuloregalis clouds appear in\Nthe southern skies the next day.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.92,0:09:06.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And judging from its five-per-month rate,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.02,0:09:10.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Knock-Up Stream will\Nprobably be active tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.69,0:09:13.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll happen somewhere south of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.63,0:09:21.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not a 100% certainty, but there's\Na good chance it'll be tomorrow!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.14,0:09:31.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to have met fools like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.28,0:09:36.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, let's go and have some food!\NTake it easy at my place today...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.72,0:09:41.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...comrades!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.62,0:09:44.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Food! Hurry, Usopp!\N--Yeah! C'mon!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.72,0:09:49.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Chopper! Go get Robin-chan!\N--Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.66,0:09:54.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Looks like all we can do is try\Nour best to get into the sky...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.20,0:09:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Though in the end, it's up to luck...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.37,0:09:59.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Nami. Am I miserable and cowardly?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.91,0:10:01.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot "stupid."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.77,0:10:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know how you feel. Now go apologize.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.88,0:10:10.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, old guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.38,0:10:18.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the...?! Yuck! Don't wipe your snot on me!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.26,0:10:23.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Today's booze is especially great!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.43,0:10:26.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eat up, eat up! The saury full\Ncourse is just getting started!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.97,0:10:28.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.67,0:10:32.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha, salvage bum!\NThat's a Tabasco Bomber!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.17,0:10:35.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you! Long-nose!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.91,0:10:37.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Girlie! Come sit here!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.74,0:10:45.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 100 years too early to\Nhave Nami-san wait on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.32,0:10:53.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I saw gold...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.56,0:10:55.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in the skull's right eye!"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.19,0:10:59.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.40,0:11:04.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That tear-soaked sentence was\Nthe last thing Noland wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.90,0:11:08.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"I saw gold in the skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.91,0:11:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland was executed that same day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.98,0:11:15.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after coming to Jaya,\Nthose words make no sense at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.01,0:11:17.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The skull's right eye..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.82,0:11:20.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it referring to the name\Nof a city that once existed?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.95,0:11:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Or was it an allusion to his own death?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.72,0:11:27.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blank pages that follow say nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.96,0:11:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why we dive!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.03,0:11:33.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have a dream! On the sea floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.73,0:11:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.44,0:11:40.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna fly!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.74,0:11:48.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not if you keep eating like that, we won't!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:51.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's gotten quite late, but I see it, Bellamy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.75,0:11:54.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to go ashore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.15,0:12:02.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dream-chasing fools deserve\Nmore than a few lumps!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.14,0:12:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The day I arrived on Jaya.\NEntry for May 21, 1122."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.91,0:12:22.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.35,0:12:25.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Upon landing on the island,\Nwe heard strange bird calls
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.32,0:12:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and the sound of a very large\Nbell coming from the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.02,0:12:37.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound from that huge\Ngold bell resonated far and wide,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.53,0:12:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,almost as if showing off the\Nprosperity of a city long past!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.57,0:12:48.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We thought we knew everything\Nafter living for a few decades..."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.04,0:12:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland! Noland!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.51,0:12:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"...but experiencing the transience\Nof this civilization that flourished
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.68,0:12:58.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for a long time on the wide\Nopen sea left us speechless!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.28,0:13:04.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sound of the bell had\Nus stopped in our tracks!"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.56,0:13:07.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Noland's so cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.86,0:13:10.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wow! A giant gold bell!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.80,0:13:16.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a minute, old guy!\NYou like Noland after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.47,0:13:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Look at this!\N--Wow! Gold bells!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.24,0:13:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, how exactly are those "giant"?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.48,0:13:28.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These aren't that bell.\NThey're bell-shaped ingots.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.11,0:13:30.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We found these three on the sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.12,0:13:31.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ingots?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.18,0:13:33.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! So there really is a city of gold!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.52,0:13:36.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They don't prove that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.19,0:13:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You could find that much gold in any old ruins.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.46,0:13:44.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it does prove that there\Nwas a civilization in this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.40,0:13:48.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ingots are made to have standardized weights.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.40,0:13:50.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which means they were used for trade.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.00,0:13:54.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. And the strange bird calls\Nmentioned before that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.87,0:13:58.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Masira!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.14,0:14:00.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Whoa! There's more?!\N--This one's huge!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.98,0:14:04.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That's all of 'em.\N--Wow! It's so pretty!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.45,0:14:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold bells and a bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.48,0:14:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you suppose they were symbols of old Jaya?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.62,0:14:14.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dunno, but I think they were\Npart of some sort of model.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.93,0:14:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This here's called a South Bird,\Nand they still exist on this island!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.40,0:14:21.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Do they have weird calls?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.60,0:14:23.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. Just like the logbook says!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:30.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sailors have long used South Birds to...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.44,0:14:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.28,0:14:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.05,0:14:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is bad! You guys! Go into\Nthe forest! The southern forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:40.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?! What're you talking about?!\NAre you crazy, old guy?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.49,0:14:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go catch this bird! Right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.42,0:14:44.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why?! What for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.92,0:14:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we need a bird?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen closely! The Knock-Up Stream\Nyou're heading for tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.36,0:14:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is located directly south of this cape.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.43,0:14:56.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How are you going to get there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.60,0:14:58.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just sail straight there, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.87,0:15:00.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the Grand Line, you know!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.94,0:15:04.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once you're on the open sea,\Nthere's no way to get your bearings!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.41,0:15:06.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.04,0:15:10.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're heading for ocean, not an island,\Nso we have no guide to rely on!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.68,0:15:13.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how do we go straight south?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.65,0:15:17.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You use that bird's behavior!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.42,0:15:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Some types of animals have\Naccurate, internal magnets
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.66,0:15:24.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which allow them to get their bearings.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.33,0:15:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're lower than an animal, Zoro!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.00,0:15:29.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you're anyone to talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.33,0:15:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,South Birds are the greatest of such animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.61,0:15:37.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how vast the land\Nor sea they're thrown into,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.71,0:15:43.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,their bodies will always indicate\Nthe direction accurately.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.25,0:15:46.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, without one of these birds,\Nyou're going nowhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:50.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You won't even get the\Nchance to go to the sky island!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.05,0:15:51.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.36,0:15:54.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.26,0:15:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Quit fussing!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.36,0:15:59.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no time! Hurry! Don't dilly-dally!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.60,0:16:02.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You want us to go into the forest\Nin the middle of the night?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.23,0:16:05.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You forgot these!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.37,0:16:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna get started on your beat-up ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.11,0:16:12.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now that I think about it,\Nthere was no time to be partyin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.38,0:16:14.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Again, why are you telling us this now?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.68,0:16:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen! Make sure you catch at\Nleast one South Bird before dawn!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.55,0:16:25.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--It's pitch dark!\N--Quit pulling me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.42,0:16:29.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault! My hands\Nare moving on their own!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.39,0:16:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My stomach's so full...\NI don't think I can chase birds...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.30,0:16:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are these weird birds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:39.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just catch one so we\Ncan get back to drinking!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.74,0:16:42.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How did we wind up doing this so suddenly?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.71,0:16:47.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--You're in the way!\N--Man! Couldn't he have told us during the day?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.05,0:16:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, where are the birds?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.21,0:16:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we knew where they were,\Nwe wouldn't be out looking for 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.05,0:16:54.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Our only clue is that they have a weird call...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.39,0:16:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they look just like that gold statue...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.42,0:17:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there really such dumb-looking birds?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.73,0:17:04.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus "weird call" is way too vague!\NHow're we supposed to know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.00,0:17:11.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said we'd know once we're in the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.24,0:17:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A weird call!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.67,0:17:13.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.01,0:17:15.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.07,0:17:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At this point, we got no other choice!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.28,0:17:20.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We have three nets. Let's split\Ninto three groups and search!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.08,0:17:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.08,0:17:25.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go! Let's beat up those weird birds!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.25,0:17:33.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You mean catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.46,0:17:36.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry! Whatever we run into,\NI'll protect you, Nami-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.83,0:17:38.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sanji-kun! What about me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.46,0:17:41.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hell if I care! Quit being insecure!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.07,0:17:45.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In any case, let's catch a bird\Nso we can get out of this forest!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.07,0:17:51.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's start by listening closely\Nfor that bird we heard earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.41,0:17:54.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--That bird call!\N--Jooo! Come out! Joooo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.01,0:17:58.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.12,0:17:59.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What're you catching me for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.92,0:18:03.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Nami! That's a cool thing\Nyou got on! Where'd you get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.39,0:18:08.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.16,0:18:09.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spider!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.76,0:18:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? It's just a spider!\NYou poor thing... Come here!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.20,0:18:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spiders are yucky, you moron!\NToss it away somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.07,0:18:20.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get away, Usopp! I bet it's poisonous!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.67,0:18:22.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're falling from the trees!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.77,0:18:24.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is too gross!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.64,0:18:27.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's probably a species of tarantula!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.11,0:18:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! They won't spit poison\Nas long as we don't do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.08,0:18:33.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I used to fight spiders a long time ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.12,0:18:37.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, you can count me out when\Nit comes to creepy bugs like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.39,0:18:41.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Same here! I totally hate them!\NTotally! Hurry and throw it far away!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.19,0:18:49.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? But those moths and\Ncentipedes don't bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.51,0:18:57.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hate moths and centipedes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.11,0:19:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ahh! Don't leave me behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.65,0:19:03.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hear screams...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.35,0:19:09.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget about 'em.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.22,0:19:11.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A centipede, huh? It's pretty damn big...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.89,0:19:15.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nice to kill everything. Poor thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.69,0:19:19.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's what it gets for trying to attack me.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:21.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--But...\N--What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.37,0:19:26.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the path we just took here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.44,0:19:29.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bird call... This way.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.71,0:19:33.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out for that quagmire.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.75,0:19:40.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Wait for--!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.25,0:19:41.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Gotcha!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.59,0:19:43.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Chopper! It's an Atlas!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.79,0:19:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Atlas?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.79,0:19:50.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup! Atlases and Hercules are\Nthe most admired bugs in the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.19,0:19:52.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really? Beetles?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.23,0:19:55.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You never heard of 'em?!\NThey're super hard to catch!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.30,0:19:57.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which is better, them or the One Piece?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.47,0:19:59.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm... That's hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.80,0:20:02.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy! There's something here, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.21,0:20:04.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! It's a Miyama!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.78,0:20:07.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Catch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It flew away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.61,0:20:12.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why, you...!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.42,0:20:16.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After it! Don't let it get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.42,0:20:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A beehive! Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.74,0:20:34.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's with this forest?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.94,0:20:37.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Luffy! Look there!\N--It's that bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.58,0:20:41.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He dropped the beehives!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.38,0:20:45.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Eh?!\N--Huh? Did he say something?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.55,0:20:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "I'll kill you for invading this forest!"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.53,0:21:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, now, boy! Don't be making us mad!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.50,0:21:09.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not nice to suddenly show up\Nat night and demand gold, kiddos.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.51,0:21:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave! We got work to do now!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.71,0:21:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're bodyguards, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.55,0:21:20.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, there was\Na pirate named Cricket...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.05,0:21:23.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the sad tale of your\NMontblanc family at the pub.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.79,0:21:25.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It moved me so.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.72,0:21:31.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Treasure someone else struggled to\Nget has a special flavor all its own!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.63,0:21:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wanna know what people call me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.07,0:21:40.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Hyena!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.20,0:21:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, beyond the never-ending sky
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.31,0:21:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The future that I once saw\Nis now starting to take shape
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.66,0:22:14.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are days where I almost lose to myself
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.17,0:22:22.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When that happened, there was\Nsomeplace warm I could go
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.55,0:22:28.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The friends I took pride in\Nalways, without fail,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.69,0:22:36.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,pushed me onwards, didn't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.70,0:22:47.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, the stars are pouring\Ndown underneath the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.97,0:22:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This unique moment...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.35,0:22:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Old guy! We caught a bird!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.18,0:23:00.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What happened, old diamond-head?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.49,0:23:02.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.45,0:23:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's nothing we could do! We're pathetic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.82,0:23:06.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The gold's been stolen!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.66,0:23:09.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright! Forget about that junk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.09,0:23:10.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bellamy's mark!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.50,0:23:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back by morning!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.16,0:23:13.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:16.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Dreams Don't Come True?!\NBellamy versus the Saruyama Alliance"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.80,0:23:24.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
